## Quick Reference

```css
/* Viewport meta tag (in HTML) */
/* <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" /> */

/* Mobile-first media queries */
@media (min-width: 640px) {  /* sm */ }
@media (min-width: 768px) {  /* md */ }
@media (min-width: 1024px) { /* lg */ }
@media (min-width: 1280px) { /* xl */ }

/* Responsive container */
.container {
  width: 90%;
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 1rem;
}

/* Fluid typography */
.fluid-text {
  font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);
}

/* Responsive images */
img {
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}
```

**Remember:**
- ✅ Always include viewport meta tag
- ✅ Use mobile-first approach
- ✅ Test on real devices
- ✅ Use relative units (rem, %, vw)
- ✅ Keep breakpoints to a minimum (3-4 max)
- ✅ Consider accessibility (zoom, font sizes)
- ❌ Don't use fixed widths for main containers
- ❌ Don't target specific devices (iPhone X, etc.)
- ❌ Don't forget to test on slow connections
